This paper discusses transmission scheduling in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the tradeoff between spectrum efficiency and user-level fairness, which is a topic that falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper proposes a fully distributed algorithm for implementing the relaxed-TDMA scheme, which is a topic that falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions LTE-advanced and WiMAX, which are topics that fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) and cryptography and security (cs.CR), respectively.
